        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extract shared LLM contracts, event streams, diagnostics, and tool validation into `packages/llm-core`.\n- Extract provider-neutral API registry and stream/complete helpers into `packages/llm-runtime`.\n- Keep existing `src/llm/*`, `packages/agent-core/src/llm.ts`, and `openclaw/plugin-sdk/llm` source entrypoints as compatibility facades while builtin providers continue registering through `src/llm/stream.ts`.\n- Add tsdown package builds for the new packages so declared dist exports are emitted by normal builds.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm test packages/llm-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/llm-runtime/src/api-registry.test.ts src/agents/custom-api-registry.test.ts src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Notes\n\n- `pnpm test:changed` was also run. It completed many routed shards but failed in the agents shard with three `src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts` assertions plus one worker OOM. The same failing file passed immediately afterward in isolation with the focused command above, so this is recorded as a broad changed-test instability rather than accepted proof failure for the patch.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: LLM shared contracts and provider-neutral registry/runtime code now live in workspace packages while existing OpenClaw source and plugin SDK entrypoints continue to resolve.\nReal environment tested: local macOS source checkout, Node via repo scripts, pnpm workspace.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm check:changed`; `pnpm build`; focused Vitest command listed above; branch autoreview listed above.\nEvidence after fix: changed check and build completed successfully; focused tests passed; autoreview returned no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: package build emits the new package dist outputs during build, source compatibility facades resolve, and registry test cleanup no longer clears builtin providers globally.\nWhat was not tested: full `pnpm test` and full `pnpm test:changed` green run; changed-test rerun hit the agents shard instability/OOM described above.\n",
